## 🚨 CRITICAL LOCAL SWARM INSTRUCTIONS
Multiple agents work in this directory on the same local machine in real-time.
1.  **NO `git add .`**: Staging everything will commit unfinished code from neighboring agents. Stage files surgically: `git add apps/web/src/components/MyComponent.tsx`.
2.  **RE-READ FILES BEFORE EDITING**: Use file viewing tools to check the live disk state of files immediately before modifying them. Neighboring agents may have edited them seconds ago.
3.  **RUN TYPECHECKS**: You MUST run `npm run typecheck` after any TypeScript modifications. Committing code that breaks the compilation is a critical failure.
4.  **RUN BIOME**: Keep formatting consistent. Run `npx @biomejs/biome check --write .` on modified files.
5.  **UTF-8 ONLY**: Writing Russian text? Use the `write_to_file` tool to write files. PowerShell here-strings and inline CLI node scripts will corrupt Cyrillic characters (Mojibake).

---

## 🏗️ SYSTEM LOCKS
*   **PGlite Database**: The database client connects locally to PGlite (a local filesystem-based Postgres engine in `apps/api/dente-db`). There is no network Postgres server on port 5432. Do not use connection pools or standard pg credentials.
*   **God Context (`useAppLogic.tsx`)**: Exposes over 500 variables and functions. Any modification to its return object or deletions of exported fields will break typechecks across dozens of UI components. Be extremely surgical.
